		<p class="prose">If you’re old enough to remember, this sounds like quintessential 2000s emo: <b>Dashboard Confessional</b> lyrics, but over a hip hop beat. This emerging sub-genre is known as “emo-rap,” and Juice Wrld’s lyrics feel just as emotionally vulnerable as Dashboard’s, the poster band of mid-2000s teenage angst.
		</p>
		<p class="prose">I wondered: <b>who has the most emotionally vulnerable lyrics, emo-rappers or Dashboard Confessional?</b> Has Juice Wrld out-emo’d emo bands?
		</p>
