	<div class="first-section post-emo-index">
		<p class="prose">My Chemical Romance’s <i>The Black Parade</i> comes out on top, but Juice Wrld’s <i>Goodbye & Good Riddance</i> and XXXtentacion’s <i>?</i> fall closely behind. For what it’s worth, both emo-rap albums are far ahead of Dashboard, Fall Out Boy, and Jimmy Eat World.
